Dr. Ray Peat tended to shit on "nootropics", but individually wrote positively on Memantine, Ginkgo, Piracetam, etc. Where the problem lies is the concept of nootropil drugs itself reinforcing Cartesian mind-body dualism. Guenon has a similar critique with transl. of Hindu texts.

E.g. Piracetam decreases lipid peroxidation and possibly has anti-proliferative effects against tumors, but thinking of it as in a specific class of drugs makes people ignore those aspects. Similarly Eastern concepts of substance and essence etc. get washed out in 17th c. jargon.
